The note - which is written in red on a white background - reads: 'No Drugs! Any one (sic) caught will be banned for life.'

Officers from West Midlands Police seized the drugs, which will now be destroyed, but no arrests were made.

'At around 1.45pm officers located around 110 cannabis plants at the Laffin Few pub in High Street, Tipton,' said a spokesman.

'The plants have now been removed and seized.

